It is the public policy of this Commonwealth that a public servant shall work for the benefit of the people of the Commonwealth. The principles of ethical behavior contained in this chapter recognize that public office is a public trust and that the proper operation of democratic government requires that:
A public servant be independent and impartial;
Government policy and decisions be made through the established processes of government;
A public servant not use public office to obtain private benefits; and
The public has confidence in the integrity of its government and public servants.
